{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"93e0f902-47d4-4cc7-9027-5de0012f6c57","title":"Serverless Framework","desc":"","updated":1639649948370,"created":1617588356217,"stub":false,"custom":{"stub":false},"fname":"tools.serverless","type":"note","vault":{"name":"main","fsPath":"main","useFMTitle":false},"contentHash":"9578bfd0ac37f34fd9d18b117c42baba","links":[],"anchors":{"serverless-framework":{"type":"header","text":"Serverless Framework","value":"serverless-framework","line":9,"column":0,"depth":1},"memory-leak-in-serverless-offline-since-680":{"type":"header","text":"Memory Leak in Serverless-Offline since 6.8.0","value":"memory-leak-in-serverless-offline-since-680","line":11,"column":0,"depth":2},"v2-uses-locally-installed-package-over-global-package":{"type":"header","text":"V2 Uses Locally Installed Package Over Global Package","value":"v2-uses-locally-installed-package-over-global-package","line":17,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":["563ce103-bde6-4e92-b41a-184940dace74"],"parent":"4fb536a9-c146-4df3-8f30-9b2fb52a77f7","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"serverless-framework\">Serverless Framework<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#serverless-framework\"></a></h1>\n<h2 id=\"memory-leak-in-serverless-offline-since-680\">Memory Leak in Serverless-Offline since 6.8.0<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#memory-leak-in-serverless-offline-since-680\"></a></h2>\n<p>There is a <a href=\"https://github.com/dherault/serverless-offline/issues/1119#issuecomment-876463656\">memory leak</a> in Serverless-offline which leaks memory after an endpoint is invoked. Fortunately, there is a simple workaround for this, per the linked comment.</p>\n<p>Add the <code>--allow-cache</code> option if running from CLI or edit serverless config to add <code>allowCache: true</code> to Serverless-offline options.</p>\n<h2 id=\"v2-uses-locally-installed-package-over-global-package\">V2 Uses Locally Installed Package Over Global Package<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#v2-uses-locally-installed-package-over-global-package\"></a></h2>\n<p>This caught us unaware. CI pipeline does <code>npm -i g serverless</code> to install v2.x but package.json specified an older v1.x version.</p>\n<p>I couldn't figure out why it was using an older version until coming across the <a href=\"https://www.serverless.com/blog/serverless-framework-v2\">v2 blog post describing this breaking change</a> - if both a global and local install is available, the local one will be used.</p>\n<hr>\n<strong>Children</strong>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/563ce103-bde6-4e92-b41a-184940dace74\">Using Serverless Framework With Aws</a></li>\n</ol>","noteIndex":{"id":"root","title":"root","desc":"","updated":1622102326440,"created":1595961348801,"stub":false,"custom":{"stub":false,"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"name":"main","fsPath":"main","useFMTitle":false},"contentHash":"2222728f026e86e75d06a6048c4f43ed","links":[],"anchors":{"personal-knowledge-base":{"type":"header","text":"Personal Knowledge Base","value":"personal-knowledge-base","line":9,"column":0,"depth":1}},"children":["9fa47ef8-a44b-4e36-929f-4aa7835b474d","6e43ea37-b3e7-44cf-aac7-31ae947d32a2","a10a1802-11d0-4557-a374-89712109cf90","0b9beaed-19ee-4124-a880-07e520da2b17","ddf3e9b2-ea12-4129-8785-06d6b82d4fcb","k6cqa8os92v51eze0j04mb4","5uawuvtmz4i2p2pixnjt11r","b4be93a8-69e3-4427-b4cd-53593c3ab387","5bbec2d1-4abe-4a2a-8bc5-5f3d4e229766","4a064a97-3d2d-4429-9a08-5b158dc7ef35","543e830d-feac-4048-8075-58c406bc1105","8875d2cf-85f8-41e8-b16d-c3707e40d74e","4k2ot7nwcxbum3rwhovp8bp","8ec37b11-59ad-4ea8-82d9-3186e7e0cd29","dOehc8Yap1zIbEqLvQvOt","b58269ed-9a0e-4213-b5b0-6d59c81d9899","b4fc6d48-17ae-4764-acdb-ec0f52707860","091b67bf-8bfa-454c-bbd3-7d84d8216229","f6fbee87-be27-471c-99bd-4af45d6a3156","fb9e4130-eaf8-425d-9039-5bc2ee876f18","4fb536a9-c146-4df3-8f30-9b2fb52a77f7","4cwalqweyykqziy3znsqelc","jdry0g5gsm21oeh2gjpt54c","